SIMPLE: efficient
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: efficient
<hw>ef*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧f*f⟦icr⟧sh"⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>efficiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>efficere</ets> to effect: cf. F. <ets>efficient</ets>. See
<er>Effect</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Causing effects; producing
results; that makes the effect to be what it is; actively operative; not
inactive, slack, or incapable; characterized by energetic and useful
activity; <as>as, an <ex>efficient</ex> officer, power</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>efficient</qex> cause is the working cause.</q>
<rj><qau>Wilson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Effective; effectual; competent; able; capable;
material; potent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 473 --></p>

<p><ent>Efficient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Efficient
<hw>Ef*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An efficient
cause; a prime mover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God . . . moveth mere natural agents as an <qex>efficient</qex>
only.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Efficiently</ent>⟦br⟧
